format:
<style>
    /* Center the group container with class "Account" */
    .nr-dashboard-cardpanel.Account, .nr-dashboard-cardcontainer.Account {
    //display: flex;
    justify-content: center; /* Centers horizontally */
    align-items: center; /* Centers vertically */
    //height: 45vh; /* Make the container take the full viewport height */
    }
    
    /* Ensure individual cards inside the container are properly centered */
    .nr-dashboard-cardcontainer.Account md-card {
    margin: 10px; /* Add some margin around each card for spacing */
    }
    
    /* Additional styling to make sure content inside the card is centered */
    .nr-dashboard-cardcontainer.Account .nr-dashboard-widget {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center; /* Centers content horizontally */
    align-items: center; /* Centers content vertically */
    }
    /* Center the welcome text and position it at the top of the group */
.nr-dashboard-cardpanel.Account .Welcome {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center; /* Centers horizontally */
    align-items: center; /* Centers vertically */
    text-align: center; /* Ensures text inside the div is centered */
    width: 100%; /* Ensures the div takes full width */
    position: absolute; /* Positions the div absolutely within the container */
    top: 0; /* Positions the div at the top */
    margin-top: 10px; /* Adds some margin at the top if needed */
    font-size: 24px; /* Adjust the font size as needed */
}

/* Optional: Adjust the padding or margin of the group if needed */
.nr-dashboard-cardpanel.Account {
    padding-top: 50px; /* Adjust this value based on your design */
    position: relative; /* Ensure the group is relatively positioned for the absolute child to work correctly */
}

    
</style>

name: Select User

format:
<style>
    #go-fullscreen-btn {
        height: 100%;
        border-style: unset;
    }
    .btn-parent {
        padding: 0 !important;
    }
</style>
<md-button id="go-fullscreen-btn" ng-click="send({payload:action('go fullscreen')})" type="button">Go Fullscreen
</md-button>
<script>
    fsElem = document.documentElement;
    theParentElem = document.getElementById("go-fullscreen-btn").parentNode
    theParentElem.classList.add('btn-parent')
    
    this.scope.action = function(params) {
    console.log("params received is: ",params)
    if (fsElem.requestFullscreen) {
        fsElem.requestFullscreen();
        } else if (elem.mozRequestFullScreen) { /* Firefox */
        fsElem.mozRequestFullScreen();
        } else if (elem.webkitRequestFullscreen) { /* Chrome, Safari and Opera */
        fsElem.webkitRequestFullscreen();
        } else if (elem.msRequestFullscreen) { /* IE/Edge */
        fsElem.msRequestFullscreen();
        }
    // In fullscreen. Now hide the button.
    document.getElementById("go-fullscreen-btn").classList.add('ng-hide');
    return {payload:"Fullscreen is active."}
    }
</script>

name: Select User

format:
<style>
    #go-fullscreen-btn {
        height: 100%;
        border-style: unset;
    }
    .btn-parent {
        padding: 0 !important;
    }
</style>
<md-button id="go-fullscreen-btn" ng-click="send({payload:action('go fullscreen')})" type="button">Go Fullscreen
</md-button>
<script>
    fsElem = document.documentElement;
    theParentElem = document.getElementById("go-fullscreen-btn").parentNode
    theParentElem.classList.add('btn-parent')
    
    this.scope.action = function(params) {
    console.log("params received is: ",params)
    if (fsElem.requestFullscreen) {
        fsElem.requestFullscreen();
        } else if (elem.mozRequestFullScreen) { /* Firefox */
        fsElem.mozRequestFullScreen();
        } else if (elem.webkitRequestFullscreen) { /* Chrome, Safari and Opera */
        fsElem.webkitRequestFullscreen();
        } else if (elem.msRequestFullscreen) { /* IE/Edge */
        fsElem.msRequestFullscreen();
        }
    // In fullscreen. Now hide the button.
    document.getElementById("go-fullscreen-btn").classList.add('ng-hide');
    return {payload:"Fullscreen is active."}
    }
</script>

Clock Toolbar
format:
<script id="titleScript" type="text/javascript">

$(function() {
    if($('.md-toolbar-tools').length != 0){
        loadClock();
    }else setTimeout(loadClock, 500)
});

function loadClock(){
    $('#clock').remove();
    var toolbar = $('.md-toolbar-tools');
    
    var div = $('<div/>');
    var p = $('<p/ id="clock">');
    
    div.append(p);
    div[0].style.margin = '5px 5px 5px auto';
    toolbar.append(div);

    function displayTitle(lh) {
        p.text(lh); 
    }
    
    function upTime() {
        var d = new Date();
        p.text(d.toLocaleString());
    }

    if(document.clockInterval){ 
            clearInterval(document.clockInterval);
            document.clockInterval = null;
    }
        
    document.clockInterval = setInterval(upTime,1000);
}

</script>
